[Name] PLIB
[Summary] A portable game-writing library.
[License] GNU Lesser General Public License (LGPL)
[Description] PLIB is a set of libraries to write games and other realtime interactive applications that are 100% portable across a wide range of hardware and operating systems. It's used by Majik3D, FlightGear, and others, and includes libraries for GUI widgets, sound replay, geometry, scene graph, joystick, and fonts/text.
[Homepage] http://plib.sourceforge.net/
